Plan: Switch from Claude API to Local Ollama
Context
Replace the Anthropic Claude API integration with a fully local Ollama instance for session transcript analysis. This eliminates external data transmission — all D&D session data (player names, transcripts, campaign details) stays on the local machine. Also hardens .gitignore to prevent accidental commits of sensitive data.

Ollama Setup Instructions (for the user)
Install Ollama: Download from https://ollama.com/ and run the installer
Pull a model: ollama pull llama3.1:8b (good balance of quality/speed for 12GB+ VRAM)
Alternative: ollama pull mistral (lighter, faster)
Verify it's running: ollama list and curl http://localhost:11434/v1/models
Ollama runs as a background service automatically after install
Code Changes
1. app/services/analysis.py — Swap Anthropic client for OpenAI SDK
Replace import anthropic with from openai import OpenAI
Update _call_claude → _call_llm to use OpenAI client pointing at http://localhost:11434/v1
Client init: OpenAI(base_url=base_url, api_key="ollama") (Ollama ignores the key but the SDK requires one)
Change client.messages.create(...) to client.chat.completions.create(...) (OpenAI format)
Update response parsing: response.choices[0].message.content instead of message.content[0].text
Update default model from claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 to llama3.1:8b
Reduce _CHUNK_WORD_LIMIT from 60,000 to ~6,000 (local models have smaller context windows; llama3.1:8b supports 128k but performs better with shorter inputs)
